definition: to travel around/to roam/(mobile telephony) roaming

pinyin: Ai4 li4 si1 Man4 you2 Qi2 jing4 Ji4

sentences.english: The structure of his mental perambulations also seems to have changed.
sentences.chinese: 他的思維漫遊的路線似乎也發生了變化。

sentences.english: As the rover trundled around, its wheels kicked up soil rich in sulphate.
sentences.chinese: 當漫遊車四處工作時，車輪拖出了富含硫酸鹽的泥土。

sentences.english: The park had fine trees, and there were deer roaming among them.
sentences.chinese: 獵苑裏樹木優良，鹿漫遊於樹間。

sentences.english: Tourists walk in the Summer Palace with deliberate steps.
After more than two years of wandering, Eugene returned to Moscow.
sentences.chinese: 葉甫蓋尼經過兩年多的漫遊以後又回到了莫斯科。

sentences.english: The complex scene's virtual walkthroughs is the important field in which VR is used.
sentences.chinese: 複雜場景的虛擬漫遊是虛擬現實中的重要應用領域。

sentences.english: Answer:Check the system clock on the users computer.
sentences.chinese: 你正在對一個用戶的漫遊配置文件進行疑難解答。

sentences.english: Keep an eye out for Mutalisks roaming the map as well.
When we met, you warned me of your wanderlust.
sentences.chinese: 但我們相遇之時，你就警告我說你有漫遊癖。

sentences.english: A large tiger named Pasha roams the garden.
sentences.chinese: 一個名爲大老虎帕夏漫遊花園。

sentences.english: International travelers have been gouged by high roaming fees and poor coverage for years.
sentences.chinese: 國際旅客已挖出高漫遊費和窮人的範圍內。

sentences.english: He had been knocking about the world, and living in queer corners.
sentences.chinese: 他在世界上四處漫遊，也可說是到過海隅地角。

sentences.english: I'd like to borrow a copy of Alice in Wonderland.
sentences.chinese: 我要借一本《愛麗絲漫遊奇境記》。

sentences.english: Turning, wandering night, the digger of eyes.
sentences.chinese: 轉動的，漫遊的夜，雙眼的挖掘者。

sentences.english: Where it can reflect upon its dogmatic wanderings.
sentences.chinese: 懷疑讓理性能反省其教條式的漫遊旅程。

definition: to amuse oneself/to have fun/to go sightseeing/to take a stroll
to explore/to go on an expedition/adventure
to look at sth with pleasure/to watch (sth marvelous)/ornamental
to have a taste of/to realize/to appreciate
